Description: Calcite dummy canopic jar: Qebhsenuef; four columns of incised Hieroglyphic text within a panel.
Curator's comments: The jar formed part of a set, together with EA 36534, EA 36536 and EA 36537. The source of the group, 'Sm', is noted only on the Birch Slip for EA 36539 [E.S. 639], but all four jars are inscribed with the same name and they are listed as a set in the 3-volume MS catalogue of the Sams Collection (AES archive).
